						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab built into the wall of the Kalamēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṅghaṇa—A.D. 1245.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the king's <hi rend="bold">regnal year 41, Viśvāvasu, Vaiśākha, śu. 14 Wednesday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1245, April 12, Wednesday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription records a gift of provisions to god Mallikārjuna by the <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> and others• The name of the place is partially preserved as • • <hi rend="bold">gurava,</hi> which is in all probability Alagurava.</p>						

						</summary>
